fileDesc.title: Tesla Motors to open Boulder store

NAF.raw:
Tesla Motors to open Boulder store
Tesla Motors opens a store in downtown Boulder on Friday where it will sell its high-end, all-electric cars - just the sixth sales location opened in the United States.
The San Carlos, Calif.-based maker of high-performance electric sports cars has more connections to Boulder than it simply being a potential hotbed of environmentally minded car buyers. Kimbal Musk, a Boulder entrepreneur who's CEO of OneRiot search engine company and owner of the Kitchen restaurant, is a member of the Tesla Motors board of directors and brother to Elon Musk, Tesla's CEO and chairman. The younger Musk also drove the first Tesla Motors Roadster Sport in the state, turning heads with the bright yellow two seater. Tesla Motors will have a "gallery" storefront at 915 Pearl St. in downtown Boulder. The Tesla Roadster model can go from 0 to 60 mph in 3.9 seconds and, the company claims, can push 240 miles on a charge. It has been priced at $122,000. More than 700 of them have been delivered The company's been working on a sedan, the Model S, that's much cheaper. Tesla Motors has domestic stores in Menlo Park, Calif., Los Angeles, Seattle, Chicago, New York City and, soon, Boulder. It has stores in London, Munich and Monaco. Future locations are planned in South Florida, Washington, D.C., and Toronto, according to the company.
